---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro"
---

<MainLayout>
  <main class="flex flex-col gap-4 p-8 md:p-36">
    <section>
      <p class="text-justify">
        <span class="text-accent">Marketplace:</span> Our platform provides a
        marketplace for farmers and buyers to connect and conduct business.
        Farmers can list their products on our platform, and buyers can browse
        and purchase products directly from the farmers.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <p class="text-justify">
        <span class="text-accent">Real-time price information:</span> We provide
        real-time price information to farmers and buyers, enabling them to make
        informed decisions about buying and selling agricultural commodities.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <p class="text-justify">
        <span class="text-accent">Post-harvesting services:</span> We offer
        post-harvesting services such as sorting, grading, packing, and
        transportation, which help improve the quality of produce and reduce
        wastage.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <p class="text-justify">
        <span class="text-accent">Logistics support:</span> We provide logistics
        support to ensure that products are delivered to buyers in a timely and
        efficient manner.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <p class="text-justify">
        <span class="text-accent">Sustainable farming practices:</span> We
        promote sustainable and eco-friendly farming practices, which not only
        has a positive impact on the environment but also leads to
        higher-quality crops and increased profitability for farmers.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <p class="text-justify">
        <span class="text-accent">Gender inclusivity:</span> We actively involve
        and empower women farmers in the agricultural sector and provide equal
        opportunities for women to participate in farming and related
        activities. We also provide training and education programs to women
        farmers, to help them improve their farming techniques and increase
        their yields.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <p class="text-justify">
        <span class="text-accent">Financing:</span> Buy One Gram could offer
        financing options to farmers to help them purchase inputs such as seeds,
        fertilizers, and equipment. This would help farmers to increase their
        production and improve their yields, leading to higher profits.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <p class="text-justify">
        <span class="text-accent">Crop Insurance:</span> Buy One Gram could
        partner with insurance companies to offer crop insurance to farmers.
        This would help protect farmers from losses due to natural disasters,
        pests, and other unforeseen events.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <p class="text-justify">
        <span class="text-accent">Soil Testing:</span> Buy One Gram could offer
        soil testing services to farmers to help them determine the nutrient
        content of their soil and make informed decisions about fertilizers and
        other inputs.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <p class="text-justify">
        <span class="text-accent">Market Intelligence:</span> Buy One Gram could
        provide market intelligence to farmers, including information on demand
        trends, consumer preferences, and pricing. This would help farmers to
        make informed decisions about what crops to grow and when to sell them.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <p class="text-justify">
        <span class="text-accent">Training and Education:</span> Buy One Gram
        could expand its training and education programs to include a wider
        range of topics, such as financial management, marketing, and business
        planning. This would help farmers to improve their overall business
        skills and increase their profitability.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</MainLayout>
